According to Section 67 of the Income Tax Act, 2023, the following is written:

• Royalty, license fee, technical know-how fee, income from granting 'right to use of intangible asset;
• Cash incentive paid by the Government;
• Any such income which is not classified under section 30.

These are examples of special cases where the provision of Section 67 applies in computing "income from other sources".
